    "On the other hand, Rafieizonooz et al. [122] noted that using large amounts of GGBFS can increase both creep and shrinkage in concrete.",
    "However, Jiang et al. [123] found that replacing up to 40% of cement with GGBFS prevents drying shrinkage.",
    "Additionally, Li et al. [123] highlighted that incorporating MK in concrete reduces water loss rates, thereby decreasing drying shrinkage.",
    "Microstructure analysisSCMs vary significantly in their shapes and particle sizes, which directly affect their performance in concrete mixtures.",
    "RHA consists of irregular, angular particles ranging from 20 to 150 µm, characterized by a high surface area and a non-crystalline structure that boosts its reactivity."
